      "message": "Thanks for looking into this, but I think the fix needs rework.                                                                                                                  \n                                                                                                                                                                                   \nad-\u003ename is only used as a VPP vector (%v in format.c:19 and af_xdp_log macro), never as a C string. The added \\0 is harmful: it will be emitted verbatim by %v into the formatted output.                                                                                                                                                                \n                  \nad-\u003elinux_ifname: null termination is already guaranteed by vec_validate(ad-\u003elinux_ifname, IFNAMSIZ - 1) which zero-fills any new elements — no %c, 0 needed.\n\nIMO the real bug is the missing length check: if strlen(args-\u003elinux_ifname) \u003e\u003d IFNAMSIZ, vec_validate is a no-op and there is no null terminator. The fix should be an early length check\n\n    if (strlen (args-\u003elinux_ifname) \u003e\u003d IFNAMSIZ)\n      return error;",
